column114: The Hercules is aptly named after the titanic effort and cost that went into improving the MMF200.  For a long time it was thought it wouldn't be possible to improve the design without sacrificing fire rate, ammo capacity or accuracy.  However with several breakthroughs in reverse engineered Ravager technology, the Hercules was born.  It is a monster of a sniper rifle that almost seems to channel the spirit of the ancient demi-god himself.  A weapon sure to be instrumental in the defeat of the Ravagers.

<font face=%dq%$FixedFont%dq% color=%dq%#ffffff%dq%>     Damage Per Second: 120|     Damage Per Shot: 0.4x5|     Fire Rate: 60/sec|     Ammo Capacity: 480|     Reload: 60sec|     Accuracy: 5 Degrees Spread|     Range: 130m|     Projectile Speed: 300m/s||<font face=%dq%$NormalFont%dq% color=%dq%#80c3f5%dq%>|A model of the powerful Medium Range Laser rifle based on the Fusion Blaster experimental weapon available for infantry special forces.  With the focus of the weapon changed from sheer output to something more sustainable, this line of rifles are exclusivly designed for Wing Divers and aimed at providing them a standard weapon with much lower risk involved compared to the Short Range Laser weapon platforms that Wing Divers are traditionally associated with.The series of Reflectron Lasers are somewhat of a misnomer.  Instead of a tradional Light/Heat based Laser, this weapon instead uses Ravager technology to haress electromagnetism to produce a "heavy" wave of dense particles held together by a strong magnetic force. <font face=%dq%$FixedFont%dq% color=%dq%#ffffff%dq%>     Damage Per Second: 120|     Damage Per Shot: 0.5x4|     Fire Rate: 60/sec|     Ammo Capacity: 120|     Reload: 60sec|     Accuracy: 1.5 Degrees Spread|     Range: 100m|     Projectile Speed: Instant|     Pierces Enemies||<font face=%dq%$NormalFont%dq% color=%dq%#80c3f5%dq%>|A model of the powerful Medium Range Laser rifle based on the Fusion Blaster experimental weapon available for infantry special forces.  With the focus of the weapon changed from sheer output to something more sustainable, this line of rifles are exclusivly designed for Wing Divers and aimed at providing them a standard weapon with much lower risk involved compared to the Short Range Laser weapon platforms that Wing Divers are traditionally associated with.The LARG line of Medium Range Laser Rifles leverages the platforms use of Lasers rather than bullets to take the platform in a direction no other conventional weapon could easily go.  After the laser is focused, a refractor at the end of the barrel splits the laser multiplying the area it can cover.  While this more than halves the total output of the weapon, it makes up for this by introducing another set of focusing lenses in the refractor which further limits the weapon's range but produces lasers so intense they burn straight through Giant Insect carapaces in an instant, allowing the laser to pierce through huge groups of enemies and multiplying the overall damage dealt.  However this reintroduces risk since the best place to use the weapon is directly on the front line maximising it's limited range.This version is a direct-to-manufacture model based on the original prototype.  While unrefined compared to later models it is cheap to build en mass and has a proven record against the Giant Insects 8 years ago.
